info:
  contact: {email: frikky@shuffler.io, name: '@frikkylikeme', url: 'https://twitter.com/frikkylikeme'}
  description: Automated generation of MITRE CRITs
  title: MITRE CRITs
  version: 1.0.0
  x-logo: data:image/png;base64,
openapi: 3.0.2
paths:
  tmp0:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated actor info
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma separated values in CRIT's format
        example: Domain,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: File of comma separated values in CRIT's format
        example: Domain,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp0'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push Actors
  tmp1:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated Backdoors
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma separated values in CRIT's given format
        example: name,version,description,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Csv file in CRIT's given format
        example: name,version,description,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp1'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push Backdoors
  tmp10:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated Signatures
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma separated values in CRIT's given format
        example: title,data,data_type,data_type_min_version,data_type_max_version,data_type_dependency,version,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Csv file in CRIT's given format
        example: title,data,data_type,data_type_min_version,data_type_max_version,data_type_dependency,version,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp10'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push Signatures
  tmp11:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated Targets
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma separated values in CRIT's given format
        example: email_address,firstname,lastname,email_count,department,division,status
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Csv file in CRIT's given format
        example: email_address,firstname,lastname,email_count,department,division,status
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp11'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push Targets
  tmp2:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated campaign
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma seperated values in CRIT's format
        example: name,aliases,status,modified
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: File of comma separated values in CRIT's format
        example: name,aliases,status,modified
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp2'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push Campaign
  tmp3:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated domain info
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma separated values in CRIT's format
        example: Domain,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: File of comma separated values in CRIT's format
        example: Domain,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp3'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push Domains
  tmp4:
    post:
      description: Push new events
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma seperated values in CRIT's format
        example: title,event_type,created,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: File of comma separated values in CRIT's format
        example: title,event_type,created,source,campaign,status,description
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp4'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push Events
  tmp5:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated Exploits
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma separated values in CRIT's given format
        example: name,cve,description,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Csv file in CRIT's given format
        example: name,cve,description,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp5'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push Exploits
  tmp6:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated Indicators
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma separated values in CRIT's given format
        example: value,type,threat_types,attack_types,created,modified,source,campaign,status,actions
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Csv file in CRIT's given format
        example: value,type,threat_types,attack_types,created,modified,source,campaign,status,actions
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp6'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push Indicators
  tmp7:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated IPs
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma separated values in CRIT's given format
        example: ip,ip_type,created,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Csv file in CRIT's given format
        example: ip,ip_type,created,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp7'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push IPs
  tmp8:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated Pcap files
      parameters:
      - description: Text of csv file with additional info on pcap
        example: source,related_id,related_md5,related_type,relationship
        in: query
        name: Csv Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Csv file with additional info on pcap
        example: source,related_id,related_md5,related_type,relationship
        in: query
        name: Csv File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: file of pcap data
        example: ''
        in: query
        name: Pcap
        required: true
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp8'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push PCAPs
  tmp9:
    post:
      description: Push new or updated Raw Data
      parameters:
      - description: Text of comma separated values in CRIT's given format
        example: title,data_type,upload_type,data,version,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV Text
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      - description: Csv file in CRIT's given format
        example: title,data_type,upload_type,data,version,modified,source,campaign,status
        in: query
        name: CSV File
        required: false
        schema: {type: string}
      responses:
        '200':
          content:
            application/json:
              schema: {$ref: '#/components/schemas/tmp9'}
          description: Successful request
      summary: CRITs Push Raw Data
tags:
- {name: Investigation}
